Title : Louis L. Martz
Text : '''Louis L. Martz''' (1913-2001) was [[Sterling Professor]] of English at [[Yale University]] from 1971, retiring in 1984. From 1972 to 1978 he was also acting director of the [[Beinecke Rare Book & Manuscript Library]].

From 1963 to 1997 Martz chaired the "[[Yale Edition of the Complete Works of St. Thomas More]]", himself editing volume 12 (1976), the ''[[Dialogue of Comfort against Tribulation]]''. His other scholarly publications include ''The Poetry of Meditation: A Study in English Religious Literature of the Seventeenth Century'' (1954), ''Collected Poems, 1912â€“1944'' by [[H.D.]] (1983), and ''Many Gods and Many Voices: The Role of the Prophet in English and American Modernism'' (1998).

